---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <article class="about-page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="content">

      <p>
        I'm Shriyansh Sharma, a software engineer interested in systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most of my time is spent building projects
        and studying how complex software systems are designed.
      </p>

      <p>
        I enjoy working across the boundary between software engineering and machine learning.
        Recently that has meant exploring distributed systems, developer tooling,
        AI infrastructure, and architecture-aware engineering tools.
      </p>

      <p>
        A recurring theme in my projects is understanding how things work internally.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether it's a distributed job queue, an AI agent runtime,
        a repository analysis system, or a research paper,
        I enjoy breaking systems apart, understanding their abstractions,
        and rebuilding them from first principles.
      </p>

      <h2>Current Areas of Interest</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Distributed systems</li>
        <li>Backend engineering</li>
        <li>AI infrastructure</li>
        <li>Developer tooling</li>
        <li>Systems programming</li>
        <li>Machine learning systems</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Projects</h2>

      <p>
        Some projects I'm currently working on:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Implementr</strong> : an architecture-aware platform that helps engineers move from research papers to implementation blueprints.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Distributed AI Platform</strong> : an event-driven inference platform built around Redis Streams, worker orchestration, and realtime observability.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>AI Guardrails Agent</strong> : an MCP-enabled agent runtime with policy enforcement and human approval workflows.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        This website is my engineering notebook.
      </p>

      <p>
        I use it to document projects, technical explorations,
        implementation notes, architecture decisions,
        and lessons learned while building software.
      </p>

      <p>
        You can explore ongoing work on the{" "}
        <a href="/projects">Projects</a> page,
        read technical writing on the{" "}
        <a href="/blog">Writing</a> page,
        browse source code on{" "}
        <a
          href="https://github.com/notshriyansh"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>,
        or connect with me on{" "}
        <a
          href="https://linkedin.com/in/shriyansh-sharmaa"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </a>.
      </p>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-header {
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.page-header h1 {
  font-size: 1.75rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin: 0;
  color: var(--text);
}

.content {
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: #c9d1d9;
}

.content p {
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 1.025rem;
}

.content h2 {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.content ul {
  margin-top: 0;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  padding-left: 1.25rem;
}

.content li {
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}

.content li strong {
  color: var(--text);
}

.content a {
  color: var(--text);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-decoration-color: var(--border);
  text-underline-offset: 4px;
}

.content a:hover {
  text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  color: var(--accent);
}
</style>